Note:
OpenAPI Translation Round-Trip Probe

End-to-end proof that the OpenAPI 3.x translation pipeline is REAL, not a
skeleton:

    OpenAPI source (YAML/JSON)
      -> openapi_parser    (delegates to the YAML parser, validates the
                            OpenAPI 3.x shape, produces a tagged value-cell AST)
      -> openapi_to_hir    (lowers the AST cell tree into the HIR cell tree,
                            swapping the document type tag)
      -> hir_to_openapi    (emits the HIR cell tree back to OpenAPI YAML text)

The probe feeds a representative OpenAPI 3.x document carrying: the openapi
version, an info block (title + version + description), a single path
("/users") with a GET operation (summary, a path parameter "id", and a 200
response with a description), and a components/schemas entry ("User") with
two typed properties (id: integer, name: string). It then:

  1. Parses the source to the AST cell tree and lowers it to HIR (hir1),
     asserting the root is an OAVAL_DICT cell with the expected sections and
     walking into info/paths/components to known scalars.
  2. Emits hir1 back to OpenAPI YAML text and asserts the text is non-empty.
  3. Re-parses the emitted YAML into the AST and lowers it to HIR (hir2), then
     asserts hir2 STRUCTURALLY survives: the openapi version, the info fields,
     the path string + GET method + responses 200, and the schema property
     names + types all reappear. Structural (not byte) survival is the correct
     semantic-equivalence check because the emitter pretty-prints block YAML
     whose byte form differs from the flow-style input while the meaning is
     identical.

The second-emission assertions are the load-bearing ones: they prove the
pipeline survives a full src -> AST -> HIR -> text -> AST -> HIR cycle.

Exit code: number of failed assertions (0 == all passed). No exit_with_code.
:End Note

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/openapi/openapi_parser.runa" as Parser
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/openapi/openapi_to_hir.runa" as Frontend
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/backends/openapi/hir_to_openapi.runa" as Backend
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/yaml/yaml_to_hir.runa" as YamlFrontend
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/hir.runa" as HIR
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/dictionary.runa" as Dict
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "tests/test_utils.runa" as TestUtils

Note: Value-cell kind tags (must match openapi_parser.runa)
Constant OAVAL_SCALAR as Integer is 1
Constant OAVAL_DICT as Integer is 2
Constant OAVAL_LIST as Integer is 3

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Cell navigation helpers
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
The OpenAPI AST / HIR is a tagged value-cell tree. These thin helpers let the
probe read it without repeating the unwrap boilerplate: dict_lookup resolves a
String key inside a dict cell to its value cell, scalar_text reads the String
payload of a scalar cell, and list_of returns the inner List of a list cell.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
dict_lookup: if the cell kind is OAVAL_DICT, extract the payload Dict and
Dict.get the key; otherwise 0. scalar_text: cell_payload of an OAVAL_SCALAR
cell (0 if not scalar). list_of: cell_payload of an OAVAL_LIST cell (0 if not
list).
@End Implementation

Process called "dict_lookup" takes dict_cell as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    If dict_cell is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let kind be proc cell_kind from Parser with dict_cell
    If kind is not equal to OAVAL_DICT:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let inner be proc cell_payload from Parser with dict_cell
    If inner is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc get from Dict with inner, key
End Process

Process called "scalar_text" takes scalar_cell as Integer returns Integer:
    If scalar_cell is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let kind be proc cell_kind from Parser with scalar_cell
    If kind is not equal to OAVAL_SCALAR:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc cell_payload from Parser with scalar_cell
End Process

Process called "list_of" takes list_cell as Integer returns Integer:
    If list_cell is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let kind be proc cell_kind from Parser with list_cell
    If kind is not equal to OAVAL_LIST:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc cell_payload from Parser with list_cell
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Probe entry point
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "main" returns Integer:
    Let results be proc create_test_results from TestUtils
    proc begin_suite from TestUtils with results, "OpenAPI translation round-trip"

    Note:
    Representative OpenAPI 3.x document in flow (JSON-subset) YAML so the first
    parse is indentation-insensitive. The pipeline re-emits block YAML which the
    second parse must consume.
    :End Note
    Note:
    The path is "/users/{id}" - a real OpenAPI path template carrying a brace
    parameter. This is the load-bearing case for bug #513: the shared YAML
    lexer must keep the braces as literal scalar bytes when the path key is
    re-emitted as a BLOCK-context plain scalar on the SECOND parse. The braces
    here in the FIRST (flow-style) parse appear inside a quoted scalar so they
    were never the problem; the failure was that the emitter writes the key
    UNQUOTED as a block-mapping key ("/users/{id}:"), which previously caused
    the lexer to truncate the plain scalar at the "{". The flow-context map
    cells throughout this document (e.g. {"type": "integer"}) still rely on
    flow indicators terminating scalars correctly, so this single document
    exercises BOTH contexts. A dedicated pure-block-context probe follows the
    round-trip below.
    :End Note
    Let source be "{\"openapi\": \"3.0.3\", \"info\": {\"title\": \"User API\", \"version\": \"1.2.0\", \"description\": \"Manages users\"}, \"paths\": {\"/users/{id}\": {\"get\": {\"summary\": \"Get a user\", \"parameters\": [{\"name\": \"id\", \"in\": \"path\"}], \"responses\": {\"200\": {\"description\": \"OK\"}}}}}, \"components\": {\"schemas\": {\"User\": {\"type\": \"object\", \"properties\": {\"id\": {\"type\": \"integer\"}, \"name\": {\"type\": \"string\"}}}}}}"

    Note: --- Stage 0: parse source -> AST cell ---
    Let ast1 be proc parse_openapi from Parser with source
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "parser produced OpenAPI AST", ast1

    Note: --- Stage 1: AST -> HIR (hir1) ---
    Let hir1 be proc translate_openapi_to_hir from Frontend with ast1
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "frontend produced HIR root", hir1

    Let hir1_kind be proc cell_kind from Parser with hir1
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "HIR root is a dict cell", hir1_kind, OAVAL_DICT

    Note: openapi version present in hir1
    Let v_key be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "openapi"
    Let ver1_cell be proc dict_lookup with hir1, v_key
    Let ver1_str be proc scalar_text with ver1_cell
    proc assert_string_equal from TestUtils with results, "hir1 openapi version is 3.0.3", ver1_str, "3.0.3"

    Note: info.title / info.version in hir1
    Let info_key be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "info"
    Let info1_cell be proc dict_lookup with hir1, info_key
    Let title_key be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "title"
    Let title1_cell be proc dict_lookup with info1_cell, title_key
    Let title1_str be proc scalar_text with title1_cell
    proc assert_string_equal from TestUtils with results, "hir1 info.title is User API", title1_str, "User API"

    Note: --- Stage 2: HIR -> OpenAPI YAML text ---
    Let emitted be proc generate_openapi_from_hir from Backend with hir1
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "backend produced OpenAPI text", emitted

    Let emitted_len be proc string_length from StringCore with emitted
    proc assert_greater_than from TestUtils with results, "emitted OpenAPI is non-empty", emitted_len, 0

    Note: --- Stage 3: re-parse emitted YAML -> AST2 -> HIR2 ---
    Let ast2 be proc parse_openapi from Parser with emitted
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "re-parse of emitted YAML produced AST", ast2

    Let hir2 be proc translate_openapi_to_hir from Frontend with ast2
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "re-lowered emitted YAML produced HIR", hir2

    Let hir2_kind be proc cell_kind from Parser with hir2
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "hir2 root is a dict cell", hir2_kind, OAVAL_DICT

    Note: ================= SECOND-EMISSION STRUCTURAL SURVIVAL =================

    Note: (1) openapi version survives
    Let ver2_cell be proc dict_lookup with hir2, v_key
    Let ver2_str be proc scalar_text with ver2_cell
    proc assert_string_equal from TestUtils with results, "hir2 openapi version survives (3.0.3)", ver2_str, "3.0.3"

    Note: (2) info.title + info.version survive
    Let info2_cell be proc dict_lookup with hir2, info_key
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "hir2 has info section", info2_cell
    Let title2_cell be proc dict_lookup with info2_cell, title_key
    Let title2_str be proc scalar_text with title2_cell
    proc assert_string_equal from TestUtils with results, "hir2 info.title survives (User API)", title2_str, "User API"

    Let version_key be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "version"
    Let iver2_cell be proc dict_lookup with info2_cell, version_key
    Let iver2_str be proc scalar_text with iver2_cell
    proc assert_string_equal from TestUtils with results, "hir2 info.version survives (1.2.0)", iver2_str, "1.2.0"

    Note: (3) path string + GET operation + responses 200 survive
    Let paths_key be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "paths"
    Let paths2_cell be proc dict_lookup with hir2, paths_key
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "hir2 has paths section", paths2_cell

    Let path_key be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "/users/{id}"
    Let path_item2_cell be proc dict_lookup with paths2_cell, path_key
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "hir2 path /users/{id} survives round-trip (bug #513)", path_item2_cell

    Let get_key be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "get"
    Let op2_cell be proc dict_lookup with path_item2_cell, get_key
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "hir2 GET operation survives", op2_cell

    Let summary_key be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "summary"
    Let summary2_cell be proc dict_lookup with op2_cell, summary_key
    Let summary2_str be proc scalar_text with summary2_cell
    proc assert_string_equal from TestUtils with results, "hir2 GET summary survives", summary2_str, "Get a user"

    Let responses_key be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "responses"
    Let responses2_cell be proc dict_lookup with op2_cell, responses_key
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "hir2 responses survive", responses2_cell

    Let r200_key be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "200"
    Let r200_cell be proc dict_lookup with responses2_cell, r200_key
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "hir2 response 200 survives", r200_cell

    Let desc_key be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "description"
    Let r200_desc_cell be proc dict_lookup with r200_cell, desc_key
    Let r200_desc_str be proc scalar_text with r200_desc_cell
    proc assert_string_equal from TestUtils with results, "hir2 response 200 description survives", r200_desc_str, "OK"

    Note: (4) operation parameter survives (name=id, in=path)
    Let parameters_key be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "parameters"
    Let params2_cell be proc dict_lookup with op2_cell, parameters_key
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "hir2 parameters survive", params2_cell
    Let params2_list be proc list_of with params2_cell
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "hir2 parameters is a list", params2_list
    Let params2_count be proc size from List with params2_list
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "hir2 has exactly one parameter", params2_count, 1
    Let param0_cell be proc get from List with params2_list, 0
    Let name_key be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "name"
    Let pname_cell be proc dict_lookup with param0_cell, name_key
    Let pname_str be proc scalar_text with pname_cell
    proc assert_string_equal from TestUtils with results, "hir2 parameter name survives (id)", pname_str, "id"
    Let in_key be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "in"
    Let pin_cell be proc dict_lookup with param0_cell, in_key
    Let pin_str be proc scalar_text with pin_cell
    proc assert_string_equal from TestUtils with results, "hir2 parameter location survives (path)", pin_str, "path"

    Note: (5) schema property names + types survive
    Let components_key be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "components"
    Let comp2_cell be proc dict_lookup with hir2, components_key
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "hir2 has components", comp2_cell

    Let schemas_key be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "schemas"
    Let schemas2_cell be proc dict_lookup with comp2_cell, schemas_key
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "hir2 components.schemas survive", schemas2_cell

    Let user_key be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "User"
    Let user2_cell be proc dict_lookup with schemas2_cell, user_key
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "hir2 User schema survives", user2_cell

    Let type_key be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "type"
    Let user_type_cell be proc dict_lookup with user2_cell, type_key
    Let user_type_str be proc scalar_text with user_type_cell
    proc assert_string_equal from TestUtils with results, "hir2 User schema type survives (object)", user_type_str, "object"

    Let properties_key be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "properties"
    Let props2_cell be proc dict_lookup with user2_cell, properties_key
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "hir2 User properties survive", props2_cell

    Let id_key be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "id"
    Let idprop_cell be proc dict_lookup with props2_cell, id_key
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "hir2 property 'id' survives", idprop_cell
    Let idtype_cell be proc dict_lookup with idprop_cell, type_key
    Let idtype_str be proc scalar_text with idtype_cell
    proc assert_string_equal from TestUtils with results, "hir2 property id type survives (integer)", idtype_str, "integer"

    Let nameprop_cell be proc dict_lookup with props2_cell, name_key
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "hir2 property 'name' survives", nameprop_cell
    Let nametype_cell be proc dict_lookup with nameprop_cell, type_key
    Let nametype_str be proc scalar_text with nametype_cell
    proc assert_string_equal from TestUtils with results, "hir2 property name type survives (string)", nametype_str, "string"

    Note: ================= BUG #513: PURE BLOCK-CONTEXT BRACE PROBE =================
    Note:
    Direct, isolated proof of the lexer fix for bug #513: a plain scalar
    containing flow indicators ({ } [ ] ,) must survive in BLOCK context,
    where per the YAML spec those characters are ordinary scalar bytes (they
    only terminate a plain scalar inside flow collections). This probe feeds a
    BLOCK-style YAML document whose mapping key AND value are the BARE,
    UNQUOTED scalar "/users/{id}" - exactly the shape the OpenAPI emitter
    produces for a templated path key. The probe drives the YAML frontend
    (yaml_to_hir) directly, which is the layer the shared lexer feeds; this
    keeps the proof scoped to the lexer behaviour and independent of the
    OpenAPI shape-gate. Before the fix the lexer truncated the scalar at "{",
    so the key/value were malformed; after the fix the literal "/users/{id}"
    appears verbatim as both the mapping key and the scalar value.
    :End Note
    Let block_source be "/users/{id}: /users/{id}\n"
    Let block_hir be proc yaml_to_hir_from_source from YamlFrontend with block_source
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "block-context YAML lowers to HIR (bug #513)", block_hir

    Let block_kind be proc get_hir_node_type from HIR with block_hir
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "block-context root is dictionary literal", block_kind, HIR_DICTIONARY_LITERAL from HIR

    Let block_entries be proc get_dictionary_entries from HIR with block_hir
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "block-context dictionary has entries", block_entries
    Let block_count be proc size from List with block_entries
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "block-context mapping has exactly 1 entry (scalar not split on braces)", block_count, 1

    Let block_e0 be proc get_at from List with block_entries, 0
    Let block_k0 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with block_e0, 0
    proc assert_string_equal from TestUtils with results, "block-context key '/users/{id}' survives literally (bug #513)", block_k0, "/users/{id}"

    Let block_v0 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with block_e0, 8
    Let block_v0_str be proc get_string_literal_value from HIR with block_v0
    proc assert_string_equal from TestUtils with results, "block-context value '/users/{id}' survives literally (bug #513)", block_v0_str, "/users/{id}"

    Note: ================= FLOW-CONTEXT REGRESSION GUARD =================
    Note:
    Confirm flow indicators STILL terminate plain scalars in FLOW context. A
    valid OpenAPI doc carries the User schema written as a FLOW map whose
    properties is a flow map of two entries: {id: {type: integer}, name:
    {type: string}}. Each inner flow value must tokenize as a distinct entry
    with its own scalar - if the flow_depth guard were wrong (never tracked),
    the value of "id" would swallow ", name: ...}" and the property map would
    collapse to a single malformed entry. We assert both inner scalars survive
    with their exact text, proving flow indicators are still honored as
    terminators inside flow collections.
    :End Note
    Let flow_source be "{\"openapi\": \"3.0.3\", \"info\": {\"title\": \"T\", \"version\": \"1\"}, \"paths\": {}, \"components\": {\"schemas\": {\"User\": {\"type\": \"object\", \"properties\": {\"id\": {\"type\": \"integer\"}, \"name\": {\"type\": \"string\"}}}}}}"
    Let flow_ast be proc parse_openapi from Parser with flow_source
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "flow-context doc parses", flow_ast
    Let flow_hir be proc translate_openapi_to_hir from Frontend with flow_ast
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "flow-context doc lowers to HIR", flow_hir
    Let flow_comp_cell be proc dict_lookup with flow_hir, components_key
    Let flow_schemas_cell be proc dict_lookup with flow_comp_cell, schemas_key
    Let flow_user_cell be proc dict_lookup with flow_schemas_cell, user_key
    Let flow_props_cell be proc dict_lookup with flow_user_cell, properties_key
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "flow-context properties map present", flow_props_cell
    Let flow_id_cell be proc dict_lookup with flow_props_cell, id_key
    Let flow_id_type_cell be proc dict_lookup with flow_id_cell, type_key
    Let flow_id_type_str be proc scalar_text with flow_id_type_cell
    proc assert_string_equal from TestUtils with results, "flow-context id type is exactly 'integer' (flow indicators still terminate)", flow_id_type_str, "integer"
    Let flow_name_cell be proc dict_lookup with flow_props_cell, name_key
    Let flow_name_type_cell be proc dict_lookup with flow_name_cell, type_key
    Let flow_name_type_str be proc scalar_text with flow_name_type_cell
    proc assert_string_equal from TestUtils with results, "flow-context name type is exactly 'string' (flow indicators still terminate)", flow_name_type_str, "string"

    proc print_summary from TestUtils with results
    Let failed be proc get_failed from TestUtils with results
    proc destroy_test_results from TestUtils with results

    Return failed
End Process
